  "text": "The claustrum is located deep to the insular cortex in the human brain, and electrical stimulation of the claustrum leads to secondarily generalized seizures in the kindling model of MTLE [CITATION_1] . Lesions of the claustrum delay the development of amygdala kindling and reduce the severity of kindled seizures from generalized to partial seizures [CITATION_2] . Moreover, magnetic resonance spectroscopy imaging has shown decreased N-acetylaspartate/creatine (NAA/Cr) ratios bilaterally in the claustrum in humans with MTLE vs. control subjects, suggestive of neuronal mitochondrial dysfunction in this area in MTLE.",
